Well yes and no... I have removed heads without lowering the engine
BUT.  it is a lot easier to yank the engine and you can fix other things
while you have it out.

> gasket(s) will i need to purchase before i start?  another thing--i was 

for a head removal, you would need the new Vitron push rod tube seals, and
new exhaust copper gaskets that is probably about all you REALLY need and
some folks say you can reuse the copper exhaust gaskets but I have never
been able to get a used one to seal properly, and their cheap

> reading the article   "Hydraulic Lifters and Type IV Pushrod Tube Seals" by 
> John Anderson from the type2 library and i was wondering where i can find the 
> Viton seals that he mentioned.  This is what he suggested doing:  "Do the 

the seals are avaliable and just about everything else you need from most
of the major dealers, I get mine usually from Bus Depot, but Rocky
Mountain Motor works and all the rest have em 

> above-- the Viton seals, the gaskets needed for the head and valve seals?

now "valve Seats" if that is what you need have to be put in by a trained
and experienced machinist.  but from the way you are talking I suspect you
mean something else.

